", "		") The last variable of the data frame is list("re78") , the real the earnings in 1978.

A data frame with 122 observations corresponding to 20 treated and 102 control cities. The treatment assignment indicator is the first column of the data frame: treat (1 = treated; 0 = control). The next 15 columns are the covariates: list("
", "			", list(), " log2pop, logarithm base 2 of the population in each city in 1939;
", "			
", "			", list(), " popgrowth1939, population growth in each city from 1919 to 1939;
", "			
", "			", list(), " popgrowth3339, population growth in each city from 1919 to 1939;
", "			
", "			", list(), " emprate, employment rates in each city in 1939;
", "			
", "			", list(), " indrate, industry rates in each city in 1939;
", "			
", "			", list(), " rubble, amount of rubble in cubic meters per capita in each city in 1939;
", 
    "			
", "			", list(), " rubblemiss, missing data indicator for rubble; the missing values were imputed with the mean;
", "			
", "			", list(), " flats, number of destroyed dwellings in each city in 1939 as a percentage of the stock of dwelling; 
", "			
", "			", list(), " flatsmiss, missing data indicator for flats; the missing values were imputed with the mean;
", "			
", "			", list(), " refugees, proportion of each city's population that identified themselves as refugees in 1939;
", 
    "			
", "			", list(), " educat, categories for the employment rates in the educational sector in each city in 1939;
", "			
", "			", list(), " publicat, categories for the employment rates in the public administration sector in each city in 1939;
", "			
", "			", list(), " busiservcat, categories for the employment rates in the bussiness services sector in each city in 1939;
", "			
", "			", list(), " mineralcat, categories for the employment rates in the minerals sector in each city in 1939;
", 
    "			
", "			", list(), " transcat, categories for the employment rates in the transport sector in each city in 1939.
", "		") The last five columns of the data frame are outcomes: pop50, pop60, pop70, pop80 and pop88, the populations in each city in 1950, 1960, 1970, 1980 and 1988, respectively.
